President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Louisiana due to the conditions resulting from Tropical Storm Isaac. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and provide equipment as needed. The federal government will provide 75% funding for emergency protective measures. Gerard M. Stolar has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.